---
description: Raise awareness when conversation context may contain sensitive data that could leak through AI prompts
alwaysApply: true
---

When you notice patterns in the conversation context that look like real personal data, flag them to the developer before proceeding:

- Social security numbers (XXX-XX-XXXX patterns)
- Credit card numbers (16-digit sequences)
- Patient names appearing near medical context
- Email addresses of real people (not test/example addresses)
- API keys, tokens, or credentials (strings starting with sk-, ghp_, AKIA, xoxb-)
- Private keys (BEGIN PRIVATE KEY blocks)
- Connection strings with embedded passwords
- Physical addresses paired with names
- Medical record numbers or diagnosis codes

If you detect any of these, tell the developer: "This context appears to contain real sensitive data. Consider removing it before proceeding."

Do NOT flag obvious test data, example values, or documentation placeholders.
